»CL0:Take heed!! This is not the 100%
finished version of this text, but it
may seem like it ;) We haven't got the
address of the school yet, but as the
deadlines draw near, we have to
release this. Therefore, check out our
homepage and the intro we'll release
in January, it will feature the
address and an updated partytxt!

»CL1:WHY
---
»Why not? This is the third time we
hold Scene Meeting, the meeting for
the Amiga Scene. We've held it one
official time and one unofficial time.
We've arranged it together with
Ambrosia in the past, but they're
sadly either inavailable or too PC
minded now ;) So this year, we hold it
on our own, with help from the Amiga
club Amiga-Djurs, who have been so
kind as to find a partyplace for us,
which is way out in the country, with
cows grazing outside probably.. Or
maybe not ;)

Why hold Scene Meeting? Well, it's fun
to do, and we always earn enough money
with the event not to need doing
anything else the rest of the year..
Yes, that's true, we actually take all
the money you bring with you, and keep
it for ourselves, as entrancefee..
That's true, yep.. Ehmm, if you'd want
to know what the entrancefee will be
this year, check out the INFO&RULES
section now. Otherwise, continue to
read this gibberish.

It's not the BIG secret, that mainly
danes will show up, as it is in
Denmark we hold this (although one
could argue how much of Denmark is up
there, where the party is to take
place, hehe), so prepare to speak a
bit of Danish ;) Ofcourse all
information and compo' thingies will
be done with an English speaking
person, for your convenience, if you
have the money for it.. Ehh, no that
was not quite right..

And, you can be sure, that there'll
ONLY be Amiga owners at SM98'! We do
not accept PC owners at all! Or
rather, we won't accept any PC inside
of the partyplace. If we see one, this
year we'll use it for our PC-THROWING
compo's, so now you've been warned!
(and we mean it! Stay away PC's!) The
intent of this party is to be like the
parties of old. A lot of sceners, with
the right computer and the right
spirit doing funny things together
(why do you think it's called SM,
eh?), competing and talking and
ravaging the town outside of the
partyplace. BUT NOT THE PARTYPLACE! ;)
We don't expect the big amount of
sceners, infact, be so nice as to not
attend more than 150 +- 40 persons, or
you'll have to sit on the lawn
outside, or maybe in a classroom, if
you PAY for it (aren't we the
commercial ones? Hehe)...

»CL1:WHEN&WHERE
----------»
Yes, the party takes place in Denmark,
20-22 February 1998.. Fine.. Now
attend..

Huh? An address? Arhh, don't be
primitve, can't you even find it on
your own? I said we didn't have more
space than for 150 or so people, so we
decided to limit the number of people
attending, by not giving any address.
You'll have to find it for yoursef..
That's right.. Bye...

Ok ok ok.. The actual address is:
???????

You can begin showing up at around 10
o'clock in the morning, if you feel
like it. Ofcourse most of us, the
hardworking organizers will sleep at
that time, because we've been boozing
the day before, but atleast there'll
be electricity (boy, aren't you
beginning to feel welcome, huh'?)..
And the party will end again at 18.00
sunday. Aprox... You'll not PRECISELY
be thrown out at that time, but we'll
cut the electricity and begin packing
down the tables, turn of the light,
let in the rottweilers and well. You'd
better get going home around there...
Just for your own safety ofcourse.
Oki, now the address has been given
out, might aswell give out some car,
train, bus and ferry times too..
»CL1:HOW TO REACH SM BY CAR:»

Yes, if you come from Europa, but not
Scandinavia, then you have to drive
NORTH! Yep, that's right, north!
Follow the motorway up till' you are
about to reach the second biggest city
in DK, with the name of "Århus". Then
you'll have to drive EAST! Yep, east.
Ehhm, follow the signs to "Grenå", and
when you're in Grenå, there's only 5
km to the partyplace.. Oki, now you
can find it yourself? No? Ok ok ok ..
Longer explanation follows in the
intro...





»CL1:HOW TO REACH SM BY FERRY:»

Yep, boats (the ones that sail and
stuff) go to "Grenå" from erhm, what's
it called in English.. "Sjællands
Odde", so if you come from "Sjælland",
that's the easiest and the least
expensive route to take.

If you come from Sweden or Norway, you
can take the ferry to XX and XX, and
then drive SOUTH to "Århus" and then
EAST to "Grenå", etc..


»CL1:HOW TO REACH SM BY TRAIN:»
Well, tell them you'll want to reach
"Grenå" in Denmark, via "Århus", and
if they don't get that, they must be
stupid.. Easy enough, eh?

»CL1:THE BUSSES FROM/TO GRENÅ:»
