COMPETITIONS
------------

For all competitions we will use an
Amiga 4060, 50mhz and ENOUGH fastram,
to show the various things, but the
things MUST be able to run at the
specified minimumconfiguration stated
in the various compo's coming up. Else
you can't compete.. And you have to be
at the party to get the prizes. If you
aren't, but you win, you'll still have
the honour of winning, but the money
will be passed down amongst those
actually present..

AMIGA DEMO
----------

Must not exceed 5mb of packed size.
Must run from progdir: without
assigns. Will be shown to the end,
scrollers/plotters not included.  Must
work on an Amiga 1200 with a 50mhz
030'er and 8mb of FastRAM.

Responsible for Amiga Demo: Darkhawk

AMIGA INTRO
-----------

Will be held with 2 or more intros,
but then there WON'T be prizes for all
3 entries, heh. They must be able to
run on an Amiga 1200 with a 50mhz
030'er and 4 mb of FastRAM. The size
limit  is 40k, NOT 64k.. Make a demo
instead, if you have a 64k intro ready
;)

Responsible for Amiga Intro: Darkhawk

4 CHANNEL MUSIC COMPETITON
--------------------------

This is your standard, run of the mill
Protracker module compo. Modules up to
880k unpacked are allowed, the tune
will be played for 5 minutes, if too
many entries are delivered, a  quite
competent jury will be selected to
bring down the number  of competing
modules to 15. Ofcourse only one
module for each musician.

Responsible for the 4 Channel Music
Competition: Notman

MULTI CHANNEL COMPETITION
-------------------------

If enough modules are delivered (3 or
4), we'll have this compo too. Your
modules can be made in whatever AMIGA
musicprogram you want, that uses more
than 4 channels. Otherwise, it's the
same rules as the 4 channel compo..
Only the first ranked will get any
prize though. The others will have to
be satisfied with the extreme honour
of it ;)

Responsible for the Multi Channel
Music Competition: Notman

GRAPHICS COMPETITION
--------------------

Only iff pictures accepted, NO
raytracings (see the raytracing  compo
later), clearly digitized/scanned
pictures will be disqualified, drawn
copies are ok though. Only one picture
per graphician.

Responsible for the Graphics
Competition: Ransom

BEST RAYTRACING
---------------

All formats will be displayed if
possible. There'll only be one "real"
prize that is, but we might give the
secondplace a liter of milk or
something too! ;)

Responsible for the Best Raytracing
Competition: Ransom

SURPRISE COMPO'S
----------------

These will be held if we'll manage to
come up with something out of the
ordinary, but apart from that, we're
open for suggestions, game
tournaments, etc..

Responsible for Surprise Compo's:
Various


PRIZES
------

Yes yes, now your eyes are gleaming
with greed, eh, and all the big groups
start calculating if they all can get
their trip refunded, if they win the
democompetition. Well, as you have
seen now, the entrance is for free, so
where do we get money? Quite easy,
we're using all the money we won with
our demo Kilkenny at an earlier party,
so we have a prizebudget of 4500 Dkr,
aprox, not counting some games we won
too, and unforeseen expenses. I can
tell you the percents of the money,
that each compo will receive, ->IF<-
there's enough entries. If there isn't
enough entries, we'll use some of the
money in other competetions, but if
you e.g had a demo finished, and
release it at SM anyway, you'll get
SOME recompense, never fear!

Amiga Demo:     50%
Amiga Intro:    25%
Amiga 4Channel: 12%
Amiga Graphics: 12%

(HARHARRR!! We'll keep one percent of
our own money for ourselves, maybe..
BOY are we capitalistic!)

Raytracing, Multichannel and Surprise
compo's will get from another pool of
ressources, that we have ready. You
won't be disappointed though (or
you'll get your entrancefee back!
Hahah)...

And yes, I think that even if we
manage to win some more competitions
before the next SM, the next SM will
feature entrancefees. This is just a
commercial trick to get you to attend
NOW, and next year, we'll have an
entrancefee of 400 Dkr per person per
day! (Then again.. Maybe not..)

That's it, that's all! Now attend damn
you!
